Ellerman House, a luxury hotel in Cape Town, offers a number of travel experiences for its guests, with its White-Desert experience – a trip to Antartica via private jet – arguably the standout. Speaking to BusinessTech, a spokesperson for Ellerman House said that the hotel has seen an overwhelming response to the experience since it started promoting the trip in 2017. White Desert is the only company in the world to offer a private jet service to Antarctica. Trips vary – ranging from 24 hours to eight days – with all flights landing at Wolf’s Fang in Antartica. The Greatest Day White Desert’s ‘Greatest Day ‘ package allows travellers to visit Antartica for 24 hours. Guests first stay at Ellerman House in Bantry Bay (from one to three nights or more – depending on the clients’ needs) before departing for Wolf’s Fang. The Gulfstream has space for up to 12 guests and members of the White Desert staff will accompany guests on the flight. Travellers can choose to pay $16,000 (R224,442) for a seat, or opt to charter the flight for $225,000 (R3.1 million). As part of the trip guests receive: Return transfers for Antarctica flights; Return flight to Antarctica; All accommodation, food and drink (including all alcohol) in Antarctica; All guiding fees, support of field guides and logistics staff; The use of certain items of polar clothing, as denoted on the equipment list; Payment by White Desert of a ‘carbon tax’ for offsetting emissions created by all logistics associated with Antarctic travel. <img class="size-full wp-image-310144 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Trip.png" alt="" width="874" height="651" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Trip.png 874w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Trip-300x223.png 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Trip-768x572.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 8